Name.repository: Louise M. Darling Biomedical Library. History and Special Collections for the Sciences
Title: History and Special Collections for the Sciences Collection
Summary: Library Special Collections documents the history of scientific discoveries and inventions, research trends, communities, and communications, and teaching methods and materials in medicine and its allied health fields and the biological sciences, all of which advance UCLA's research, teaching, and learning mission. The various collections of the History and Special Collections Division support the study of the history of medicine and biology. Collections consist of books, journals, manuscripts, prints, portraits, and medical artifacts.
